cctv-viewer (2.2.6-1) jammy; urgency=medium

  * Removed "Automatically collapse top bar" option from Settings. Now, the top bar in Live windows (both main and auxiliary) collapses by default on startup, and the pin button pins it volatilely (in-memory) and locally per window without saving to disk or synchronizing across instances.
  * Implemented Auxiliary Window Limit (configurable 0-3) with a themed limit exceeded warning popup matching SingleInstanceWarning.
  * Added subtle 1px dark-gray borders around empty viewports in the Live layout grid.
  * Secured save paths and system media configuration options behind a transient "Uaktywnij zmiany w tej sekcji" (Activate changes in this section) checkbox, which resets on settings window hide or tab switch.
  * Added highlighted celadon "otwórz folder zapisu" button upon completed recording download in Archive, and always-active quick-open shortcut buttons for snapshot and video paths in Settings (auto-creating directories if missing).

 -- arkanis <arkanis@cctv-viewer2.org>  Fri, 26 Jun 2026 11:26:00 +0200

cctv-viewer (2.2.5-1) jammy; urgency=medium

  * Resolved RAM memory leaks when switching camera layouts by automatically stopping video surface format transitions and adjusting renderer dimensions.
  * Implemented unconditional cleanup and destruction of audio outputs on player stop, recycling audio output objects to eliminate memory and thread leaks on Linux.
  * Resolved viewport zoom freezing (solid color frame) by forcing correct video availability signaling when presenting the first frame of a new stream.
  * Added global setting "Disable audio entirely" to bypass audio demuxing and decoding completely, eliminating potential audio-related overhead and leaks.
  * Optimized SystemStats panel monitoring to eliminate background memory overhead by caching process IDs and using static regular expressions.
  * Enforced aggressive Garbage Collection (gc) upon layout changes and nullified video scaling contexts (SwsContext) inside video buffers to prevent libswscale leaks.
  * Corrected resource cleanup of static configuration file watcher (QFileSystemWatcher) upon application exit.

 -- arkanis <arkanis@cctv-viewer2.org>  Thu, 25 Jun 2026 11:25:00 +0200

